summary: This is a U.S. Customs and Border Protection Person Encounter Detail record documenting Ghislaine Maxwell's entry into the United States at JFK Airport on June 23, 1997. It shows her travel details and that she was admitted as an alien resident, not referred for secondary inspection.

persons.name: Ghislaine Maxwell
persons.context: The document is a U.S. Customs and Border Protection record detailing her entry into the United States at JFK Airport on June 23, 1997, showing her travel details and admission status.

events.title: Ghislaine Maxwell's Entry into the U.S.
events.description: Ghislaine Maxwell arrived at JFK Airport Terminal 3 on an inbound flight and was processed by U.S. Customs and Border Protection. She was admitted into the United States and was not referred to another agency for secondary inspection.

keyFacts: Ghislaine Maxwell entered the United States at JFK Airport on June 23, 1997, at 5:41 PM Eastern Time.
She was traveling on an Alien Registration Card (green card) and was admitted into the country.
The CBP record indicates she was processed as 'INBOUND' and was 'NOT REFERRED' to another agency for secondary inspection.
